.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxComboBox() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBcanCopy(This) -> boolean() when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the selection can be copied to the clipboard.


.RE
.B
\fBcanCut(This) -> boolean() when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the selection can be cut to the clipboard.


.RE
.B
\fBcanPaste(This) -> boolean() when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the contents of the clipboard can be pasted into the text control.

.PP
On some platforms (Motif, GTK) this is an approximation and returns true if the control is editable, false otherwise.


.RE
.B
\fBcanRedo(This) -> boolean() when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if there is a redo facility available and the last operation can be redone.


.RE
.B
\fBcanUndo(This) -> boolean() when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if there is an undo facility available and the last operation can be undone.


.RE
.B
\fBcopy(This) -> ok when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Copies the selected text to the clipboard.


.RE
.B
\fBcreate(This, Parent, Id, Value, Pos, Size, Choices, [Option]) ->\fR
\fB                boolean()\fR
\fB                when\fR
\fB                    This :: wxComboBox(),\fR
\fB                    Parent :: wxWindow:wxWindow(),\fR
\fB                    Id :: integer(),\fR
\fB                    Value :: unicode:chardata(),\fR
\fB                    Pos :: {X :: integer(), Y :: integer()},\fR
\fB                    Size :: {W :: integer(), H :: integer()},\fR
\fB                    Choices :: [unicode:chardata()],\fR
\fB                    Option ::\fR
\fB                        {style, integer()} | {validator, wx:wx_object()}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBcut(This) -> ok when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Copies the selected text to the clipboard and removes it from the control.


.RE
.B
\fBdestroy(This :: wxComboBox()) -> ok.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Destroys the object


.RE
.B
\fBgetInsertionPoint(This) -> integer() when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Same as \fIwxTextCtrl:getInsertionPoint/1\fR.

.PP
Note: Under wxMSW, this function always returns 0 if the combobox doesn't have the focus.


.RE
.B
\fBgetLastPosition(This) -> integer() when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the zero based index of the last position in the text control, which is equal to the number of characters in the control.


.RE
.B
\fBgetValue(This) -> unicode:charlist() when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Gets the contents of the control.

.PP
Notice that for a multiline text control, the lines will be separated by (Unix-style) \fI\\n\fR characters, even under Windows where they are separated by a \fI\\r\\n\fR sequence in the native control.


.RE
.B
\fBnew() -> wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Default constructor.


.RE
.B
\fBnew(Parent, Id, [Option]) -> wxComboBox()\fR
\fB             when\fR
\fB                 Parent :: wxWindow:wxWindow(),\fR
\fB                 Id :: integer(),\fR
\fB                 Option ::\fR
\fB                     {value, unicode:chardata()} |\fR
\fB                     {pos, {X :: integer(), Y :: integer()}} |\fR
\fB                     {size, {W :: integer(), H :: integer()}} |\fR
\fB                     {choices, [unicode:chardata()]} |\fR
\fB                     {style, integer()} |\fR
\fB                     {validator, wx:wx_object()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Constructor, creating and showing a combobox.

.PP
See: \fIcreate/8\fR


.RE
.B
\fBpaste(This) -> ok when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Pastes text from the clipboard to the text item.


.RE
.B
\fBredo(This) -> ok when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
If there is a redo facility and the last operation can be redone, redoes the last operation.

.PP
Does nothing if there is no redo facility.


.RE
.B
\fBremove(This, From, To) -> ok\fR
\fB                when\fR
\fB                    This :: wxComboBox(),\fR
\fB                    From :: integer(),\fR
\fB                    To :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Removes the text starting at the first given position up to (but not including) the character at the last position.

.PP
This function puts the current insertion point position at \fIto\fR as a side effect.


.RE
.B
\fBreplace(This, From, To, Value) -> ok\fR
\fB                 when\fR
\fB                     This :: wxComboBox(),\fR
\fB                     From :: integer(),\fR
\fB                     To :: integer(),\fR
\fB                     Value :: unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Replaces the text starting at the first position up to (but not including) the character at the last position with the given text.

.PP
This function puts the current insertion point position at \fIto\fR as a side effect.


.RE
.B
\fBsetInsertionPoint(This, Pos) -> ok\fR
\fB                           when This :: wxComboBox(), Pos :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the insertion point at the given position.


.RE
.B
\fBsetInsertionPointEnd(This) -> ok when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the insertion point at the end of the text control.

.PP
This is equivalent to calling \fIsetInsertionPoint/2\fR with \fIgetLastPosition/1\fR argument.


.RE
.B
\fBsetSelection(This, N) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when This :: wxComboBox(), N :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the selection to the given item \fIn\fR or removes the selection entirely if \fIn\fR == \fIwxNOT\\_FOUND\fR.

.PP
Note that this does not cause any command events to be emitted nor does it deselect any other items in the controls which support multiple selections.

.PP
See:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxControlWithItems:setString/3\fR

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxControlWithItems:setStringSelection/2\fR

.RE


.RE
.B
\fBsetSelection(This, From, To) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          This :: wxComboBox(),\fR
\fB                          From :: integer(),\fR
\fB                          To :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Same as \fIwxTextCtrl:setSelection/3\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBsetValue(This, Text) -> ok\fR
\fB                  when This :: wxComboBox(), Text :: unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the text for the combobox text field.

.PP
For normal, editable comboboxes with a text entry field calling this method will generate a \fIwxEVT_TEXT\fR event, consistently with \fIwxTextCtrl:setValue/2\fR behaviour, use \fIwxTextCtrl:changeValue/2\fR if this is undesirable.

.PP
For controls with \fIwxCB_READONLY\fR style the method behaves somewhat differently: the string must be in the combobox choices list (the check for this is case-insensitive) and \fIwxEVT_TEXT\fR is \fInot\fR generated in this case.


.RE
.B
\fBundo(This) -> ok when This :: wxComboBox().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
If there is an undo facility and the last operation can be undone, undoes the last operation.

.PP
Does nothing if there is no undo facility.


.RE
